        <para>Cataloguing a whole periodical:</para>
        <para>. A periodical has a title, one or more (often corporate) editors, and the periodical as a whole has a place and time of publication and an extent in
            number of volumes and issues published. </para>
       
        <para>Publication of an article: An article has one or more authors, a title, and a location inside a periodical. You document
            the title of the periodical as well as the location of the article inside the periodical, however, not the periodical editors or the place and
            time of publication of the periodical. Because of the regular publication pattern of the periodical, you document the time of
            publication of the article as part of the location of the article inside the periodical.</para>
